==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tufty
<hw>Tuft"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding
with tufts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Both in the <qex>tufty</qex> frith and in the mossy fell.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Growing in tufts or clusters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where <qex>tufty</qex> daisies nod at every gale.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tug</ent>⟦br⟧
